              <title>JISC Design Studio</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5231</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/5231</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>The <a title="JISC Design Studio" href="http://jiscdesignstudio.pbworks.com/w/page/12458422/Welcome-to-the-Design-Studio" target="_blank">Design Studio </a>is a developing toolkit which draws together a range of existing and emergent resources around curriculum design and delivery and the role technology plays in supporting these processes and practices.</p>
<p>The Studio will provide access to project outcomes and outputs from the JISC <a title="JISC Curriculum Design" href="http://www.jisc.ac.uk/curriculumdesign" target="_blank">Curriculum Design</a> and <a title="JISC Curriculum Delivery" href="http://www.jisc.ac.uk/curriculumdelivery" target="_blank">Delivery</a> programmes as they are developed and will continue to be sustained as a community resource after the programmes finish.</p>
<p>The toolkit has been developed as a wiki to enable the collaborative development of project outputs in closed and open spaces as well as contributions from the wider sector.</p>
<p>The main content is public so you do not need to request access to browse resources but if you want to comment on resources a log-in is required.</p>
<p>We welcome your comments and contributions to help further develop the resource.</p>]]></description>
