              <title>Resource: Five-category course map representation</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/2481</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/2481</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>This representation enables you to view a course at "a glance". It shows the key components of the course in terms of five main facets:</p>
<ul>
<li>Guidance and support</li>
<li>Information and experience</li>
<li>Communication and interaction</li>
<li>Thinking and reflection</li>
<li>Evidence and demonstration</li>
</ul>
<p>The first being the support structure provided the next three the types of learning the student does and the last the way in which the learning is assessed.</p>
<p>Three variants of this representation are provided below:</p>
<ul>
<li>A tablular version giving further information about each of the facets, along with examples.</li>
<li>A 2-D map of the OU's KE312 course (created by Mick Jones).</li>
<li>A 3-D version which shows how both the guidance and support, and the evidence and demonstation link to all three types of learning the students does.</li>
</ul>
<p>Recently we have refined our thinking on this and have condensed the catgories into four - see<a href="/cloud/view/2971"> related cloud.</a></p>]]></description>
